<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="badly-adv">badly <strong><em>adv</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'bædli/    美 /'bædli/  </p>
<p>(worse, worst)</p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-poorly">1.★ <strong>坏地；拙劣地 (poorly)：</strong></h4>
<p>反 well  </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>Rob <strong>did</strong> very <strong>badly in</strong> the history exam.
罗布的历史考得很差。</p></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>严重地；非常：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>badly beaten at football 
在足球赛中遭到惨败</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>want / need sth badly 
急需某物</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">固定搭配</h2>
<h3 id="badly-off">badly off</h3>
<p>1.<strong>贫困的；境况不好的：</strong><br />
反 well off </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I've been quite badly off recently.
最近我经济上很拮据。</p></div>

<h2 id="_3">真题解析</h2>
<ol>
<li>It’s hard for him playing against me. I’ve got nothing to play for, but for him, he needs to win so<strong><em>_</em></strong>_(bad).  </li>
</ol>
<p>答案：
1. badly  </p></div>